---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = new Date('2026-05-10').toLocaleDateString('en-us', {
	year: 'numeric',
	month: 'long',
	day: 'numeric',
});
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Disclosure Policy"
	description="Disclosures of the commercial interests, investments, and relationships that bear on the work of Letters from the Floor."
>
	<h1>Disclosure Policy</h1>

	<p>
		Letters from the Floor is published by Ethan Reese. The following relationships are disclosed
		in the interest of transparency and editorial accountability:
	</p>

	<h2>Active commercial interests</h2>

	<p>
		<strong>Overclock Systems, Inc.</strong> — Ethan is the founder and CEO of Overclock Systems, a
		Delaware C-Corp software company in the field of sales technology, based in Boston. To prevent
		any conflict of interest, Letters from the Floor does not cover:
	</p>

	<ul>
		<li>Conversation intelligence software</li>
		<li>CRM platforms</li>
		<li>Sales engagement tools</li>
		<li>Revenue operations software</li>
		<li>AI notetakers and meeting-transcription products</li>
		<li>Sales technology vendors generally</li>
		<li>Any direct competitor of Overclock Systems</li>
	</ul>

	<p>This list is maintained conservatively. When in doubt, we decline coverage.</p>

	<h2>Investments</h2>

	<p>None at present.</p>

	<h2>Advisory positions</h2>

	<p>None at present.</p>

	<h2>Other relationships</h2>

	<p>
		The editor is a graduate of Berklee College of Music. The editor banks with Mercury and uses
		common founder tooling. None of these relationships have been or will be the subject of
		editorial coverage.
	</p>

	<hr />

	<p>
		This page is reviewed and updated quarterly, and immediately upon any new commercial
		relationship that bears on the publication's beat.
	</p>

	<p class="ui">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
</BaseLayout>
